    <item>
      <title>URL used</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/eztrackback/forum/general/url_used</link>
      <description>Hi!&#13;
&#13;
In the trackback event you currently use&#13;
&lt;code&gt;$data['url']        = 'http://' . $siteURL . '/content/view/full/' . $object-&gt;attribute( 'main_node_id' );&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
I would propose replacing that with the URL alias of the main node instead. Is there a specific reason why you use the system URL? It may be more permanent theoretically, but eZ Publish's URL translation mechanism handles object moving/renaming quite well, so I don't think this is necessary.&#13;
&#13;
Greetings,&#13;
Peter</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Peter Putzer)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/eztrackback/forum/general/url_used</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 28 Nov 2008 08:53:12 +0000</pubDate>
